    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund improved treatment and awareness of Functional Neurological Disorders",
        "additional_details": "Too many patients presenting with symptoms of FND are dismissed, and do not receive the referrals or treatment they need.\r\n \r\nFunding to increase awareness of FND should improve how this condition is diagnosed, and onward referrals and treatment. Symptoms can include:\r\n \r\nNumbness\r\nWeakness\r\nTremors\r\nBlackouts\r\n \r\nWithout any referrals to treatment centres people can be left with detrimental consequences and lead people to low moods and life-changing events without support.",
        "background": "Increased funding is required to ensure patients presenting with symptoms of Functional Neurological Disorders (FNDs) are diagnosed correctly and referred to relevant specialists to receive the treatment they need. FND can be debilitating and leave people bed bound or in a wheelchair.",
